# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# --- Format ---
# <type>       required  one of the types below
# (<scope>)    optional  noun describing the affected section of the codebase
# !            optional  appended after type/scope to flag a breaking change
# <description>          imperative, lowercase, no period, ≤50 chars
#
# --- Types ---
# feat:     new feature or user-facing capability         [MINOR in semver]
# fix:      bug fix — something was broken, now it works  [PATCH in semver]
# refactor: restructure code without changing behavior
# perf:     performance improvement — same behavior, faster
# docs:     documentation only, no runtime behavior change
# style:    formatting, naming, whitespace — no logic change
# test:     add or correct tests only, no production code
# build:    build system, dependencies, or tooling
# ci:       CI/CD pipeline changes only
# chore:    maintenance that doesn't fit elsewhere
# revert:   revert a previous commit (body: This reverts commit <SHA>)
#
# --- Body (optional, wrap at 72 chars) ---
# Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW). Imperative mood. Don't restate the diff.
#
# --- Footer (optional) ---
# BREAKING CHANGE: <summary>    — breaking API/behavior change [MAJOR in semver]
# DEPRECATED: <summary>         — mark something as deprecated
# Fixes #<issue>                — close an issue
# Refs: <reference>             — link related context
#
